FBIS4-67175 "jptdd021__l94028" JPRS-TDD-94-021-L JPRS Narcotics 9 May 1994 LATIN AMERICA PANAMA Perez Balladares Comments on Trafficking, Money Laundering Perez Balladares Comments on Trafficking, Money Laundering PA0905233794 Panama City Radio Exitosa in Spanish 2210 GMT 9 May 94 PA0905233794 Panama City Radio Exitosa Spanish BFN [News conference by Panamanian President-elect Ernesto Perez Balladares with unidentified reporters upon his arrival at the Presidential Palace; broadcast in progress--live] [Excerpts] [passage omitted] [Reporter] Drug trafficking is becoming a problem in Latin America. Panama is becoming an essential bridge for drug trafficking activities. What are you going to do to stop drug trafficking activities during your administration? [Perez Balladares] We will do all we can to stop drug trafficking activities and the use of drugs in our country. [Reporter] Including the laundering of drug money? [Perez Balladares] Yes of course. [Reporter] What measures will you implement? [Perez Balladares] Well, we will implement many measures, but this is not the right time to discuss this issue. [passage omitted]
